# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# imbobi — STAGING WEB FRONTEND ENVIRONMENT CONFIGURATION
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# INSTRUCTIONS:
#   1. Copy this file: cp .env.staging.example .env.staging
#   2. Update NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL with your API staging URL
#   3. Never commit .env.staging to git (keep secrets safe)
#   4. Run: pnpm build (to generate .next/ bundle)
#   5. Deploy to Vercel, EC2, or your hosting provider
#
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Next.js Environment: staging, development, production
NODE_ENV=staging

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# API BACKEND CONFIGURATION
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# This is the URL where your frontend sends API requests.
# The frontend runs in the browser, so the URL must be publicly accessible.
#
# Examples:
#   - Local development: http://localhost:4000
#   - EC2 instance: http://ec2-staging.imbobi.com:4000
#   - AWS: https://api-staging.imbobi.com
#   - Vercel + API Gateway: https://api.imbobi.staging.vercel.app
#
# IMPORTANT: This matches the API's CORS_ORIGIN configuration
#   See: services/api/.env.staging
#
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://localhost:4000

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# SENTRY ERROR TRACKING (Optional)
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Uncomment and add your Sentry DSN if you have error tracking enabled
# Format: https://key@sentry.io/project-id
#
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SENTRY_DSN=https://your_sentry_key@sentry.io/your_project_id

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# VARIABLE TYPES
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# NEXT_PUBLIC_* prefix → Exposed to browser (frontend)
#   ✓ Used in browser-side code, fetch() calls, components
#   ✓ Visible in DevTools, page source
#   ✓ Safe to expose (no secrets here)
#
# No prefix → Server-side only (Next.js server)
#   ✓ Hidden from browser
#   ✓ Only used in API routes and server components
#
